WEBVTT

00:02.210 --> 00:04.670
[ Sighs ]
Hey, guys.

00:04.670 --> 00:05.620
Well, hey!

00:05.620 --> 00:07.830
How was work?
What event was this?

00:07.830 --> 00:09.170
Retirement party.

00:09.170 --> 00:10.500
Oh. How'd it turn out?
Was he happy?

00:10.500 --> 00:12.120
He's retired.
His kids have moved out.

00:12.120 --> 00:14.580
He's livin' my dream, man!

00:14.580 --> 00:15.960
Tacos again, huh?

00:15.960 --> 00:18.080
Yeah, but tonight, it's
with lettuce-leaf shells.

00:18.080 --> 00:20.000
I read it on Goop.
It's how Gwyneth makes hers.

00:20.000 --> 00:21.420
Why can't you just go online

00:21.420 --> 00:23.420
and look at boobs
like other husbands?

00:23.420 --> 00:25.830
Hey, you started working
and put me in charge of dinners,

00:25.830 --> 00:26.920
but you are welcome to --

00:26.920 --> 00:29.420
No, no, no, no, no, no, no!
I'll be good.

00:29.420 --> 00:30.420
Mmm!

00:30.420 --> 00:32.380
Lettuce.

00:32.380 --> 00:34.920
Oliver, why are you doing
practice tests for the S.A.T.?

00:34.920 --> 00:36.250
You're two years away.

00:36.250 --> 00:38.040
I'm getting an early jump
on things.

00:38.040 --> 00:40.210
I'm gonna need a perfect score
to get into Harvard.

00:40.210 --> 00:41.670
Mnh-mnh, we bought
that book for Taylor.

00:41.670 --> 00:43.000
No, thank you!

00:43.000 --> 00:44.460
You need to take these
practice tests

00:44.460 --> 00:45.960
if you're gonna
get into college.

00:45.960 --> 00:48.210
You'll notice Dad has stopped
saying "good" college.

00:48.210 --> 00:49.960
I've told you this
many times.

00:49.960 --> 00:51.750
I'm just not
college material,

00:51.750 --> 00:53.250
and there's nothing wrong
with that.

00:53.250 --> 00:55.380
Greg, Taylor says there's
nothing wrong with it.

00:55.380 --> 00:57.420
So I guess that's the end
of the conversation.

00:57.420 --> 00:59.880
Teenage girls always have
the best parenting instincts.

00:59.880 --> 01:01.420
Thanks for setting us
straight, Taylor.

01:01.420 --> 01:04.170
You're welcome!
I'm changing
the Wi-Fi password.

01:04.170 --> 01:06.580
I'll reveal one character
for each hour you study.

01:06.580 --> 01:07.790
Fine-ah!

01:07.790 --> 01:10.540
[ Doorbell rings ]

01:10.540 --> 01:12.040
Surprise.

01:12.040 --> 01:13.380
What are you
doing here, Mom?

01:13.380 --> 01:15.540
Can't I just drop by
to see my family?

01:15.540 --> 01:18.670
It's not a drop-by if you
have five pieces of luggage.

01:18.670 --> 01:21.040
You know that I like to
have wardrobe choices.

01:21.040 --> 01:22.290
[ Laughs ]

01:22.290 --> 01:23.670
Oh, I wish I could be
more like you,

01:23.670 --> 01:25.580
just rolling around
in velour every day.

01:26.960 --> 01:28.290
Hi, Grandma!

01:28.290 --> 01:29.250
Taylor!

01:29.250 --> 01:30.540
Would you help me
with my bags?

01:30.540 --> 01:32.000
Mm-hmm!

01:32.000 --> 01:34.670
I'll just go get settled
in the guest room.

01:34.670 --> 01:35.670
That's my office.

01:35.670 --> 01:37.120
She thinks my office
is a guest room.

01:37.120 --> 01:39.380
She also thinks a mojito
and a pack of cigarettes

01:39.380 --> 01:40.290
is a balanced meal.

01:42.000 --> 01:45.040
Mom, it's not that we're
not happy to see you.

01:45.040 --> 01:48.330
It just might not be
the best time for a visit.

01:48.330 --> 01:51.750
I have a new job, and the kids
are getting into school.

01:51.750 --> 01:54.120
Uh, sweetie,

01:54.120 --> 01:56.880
I hear you,
and I completely understand.

01:58.170 --> 02:00.710
Which is why I plan to be
a big help around the house

02:00.710 --> 02:02.500
while I'm here.

02:02.500 --> 02:04.540
Taylor.

02:04.540 --> 02:06.170
Smile.

02:06.170 --> 02:07.880
Pretty people
should never frown.

02:07.880 --> 02:09.330
Sorry, Grandma,

02:09.330 --> 02:12.500
but Mom and Dad are trying
to force me to go to college.

02:12.500 --> 02:13.420
Well, that's stupid.

02:14.830 --> 02:16.080
All right, come with me.

02:19.620 --> 02:21.170
Greg, walk me through
this again.

02:21.170 --> 02:22.620
You'll never get away with it,
you'll get 20 years to life,

02:22.620 --> 02:24.540
and no parole.

02:24.540 --> 02:26.710
Maybe I'll wait till Anna-Kat
gets into high school.

02:32.000 --> 02:33.040
♪♪

02:34.040 --> 02:36.460
♪♪

02:36.460 --> 02:38.880
Oh, Taylor,
these are your good years.

02:38.880 --> 02:40.710
You don't have to
waste them on college.

02:40.710 --> 02:42.460
Finally,
someone who gets it.

02:42.460 --> 02:44.210
No, you're at your
peak energy, your --

02:44.210 --> 02:47.210
your peak appearance.
Travel.

02:47.210 --> 02:49.540
You could walk into
any bar in Ibiza

02:49.540 --> 02:52.040
and end up riding around
on some rich man's yacht

02:52.040 --> 02:53.540
for the next two years.

02:53.540 --> 02:55.580
Ooh.
Do I get to pick the rich guy?

02:55.580 --> 02:56.790
Not usually.

02:56.790 --> 02:59.000
Mom, you said you were
going to be helpful.

02:59.000 --> 03:00.420
This is not helpful.

03:00.420 --> 03:02.040
What?
I'm just giving advice.

03:02.040 --> 03:03.420
That's what
grandmothers do.

03:03.420 --> 03:05.830
Not in a weirdly short robe,
they don't.

03:05.830 --> 03:07.290
Taylor,
go get ready for school.

03:07.290 --> 03:09.170
Fine, but I won't
learn anything.

03:10.170 --> 03:11.750
How long are you
staying with us?

03:11.750 --> 03:14.420
I only ask because you brought
a margarita machine.

03:14.420 --> 03:16.330
Oh, yeah, that's
the Jimmy Buffett,

03:16.330 --> 03:18.880
the Jaguar of at-home
blended-drink makers.

03:18.880 --> 03:19.790
[ Chuckles ]
Mm.

03:19.790 --> 03:21.290
Oh, which reminds me,
Katie.

03:21.290 --> 03:23.330
I'm gonna need a ride
to Trader Joe's

03:23.330 --> 03:25.000
for limes and rim salt.

03:25.000 --> 03:26.460
I'm not going to
take anyone anywhere.

03:26.460 --> 03:29.290
Today is my first day off
in weeks,

03:29.290 --> 03:31.880
and I am going to soak up every
moment of "The Bachelor."

03:31.880 --> 03:33.790
Will Karen F. get a rose?
Will Karen M. get a rose?

03:33.790 --> 03:35.120
Who's there for
the right reasons?

03:35.120 --> 03:37.250
You get a rose, and you get
a rose, and you get a rose!

03:37.250 --> 03:39.120
[ Laughs ]
Anna-Kat, are you okay?

03:39.120 --> 03:40.120
You seem kind of revved up.

03:40.120 --> 03:41.830
Grandma's letting me
have coffee.

03:41.830 --> 03:43.920
Mom!
Are you insane?

03:43.920 --> 03:45.880
You cannot give
a nine-year-old coffee.

03:45.880 --> 03:47.670
You're overreacting.

03:47.670 --> 03:49.290
And if she has
any trouble sleeping,

03:49.290 --> 03:51.710
I'll just give her a few
flakes of a Kloni.

03:51.710 --> 03:53.170
It's an old
stewardess trick.

03:53.170 --> 03:55.460
You cannot say stuff like that
in front of the kids.

03:55.460 --> 03:58.670
You are such
a bad influence.

03:58.670 --> 04:00.210
Oh, stop it.

04:00.210 --> 04:02.620
People said the same thing
about Galileo.

04:02.620 --> 04:04.290
Kathryn, I must say, I'm
impressed by the reference.

04:04.290 --> 04:06.330
Greg, everyone at Katie's
high school knew

04:06.330 --> 04:09.120
that Galileo Horowitz
was not the bad seed

04:09.120 --> 04:10.420
some teachers
made him out to be.

04:10.420 --> 04:12.670
[ Cellphone rings ]

04:12.670 --> 04:14.040
Hello?

04:14.040 --> 04:16.500
Principal Ablin.

04:16.500 --> 04:19.380
Okay. I will stop by
your office

04:19.380 --> 04:21.580
when I drop the kids off
at school.

04:21.580 --> 04:23.210
Oliver, get down here!

04:23.210 --> 04:24.210
What was that?

04:24.210 --> 04:26.120
My day off
being blown to bits.

04:26.120 --> 04:27.920
Principal Ablin says
he needs to talk to me

04:27.920 --> 04:31.170
about a very serious matter
involving Oliver.

04:33.000 --> 04:34.540
What did you do?

04:34.540 --> 04:35.750
I don't know.

04:35.750 --> 04:38.080
He probably wants to give me
an award or something.

04:38.080 --> 04:39.880
It's not
for community service.

04:39.880 --> 04:42.460
Am I right?
I'm not going to
high-five that.

04:42.460 --> 04:44.620
Does this mean you're not
taking me to the store?

04:44.620 --> 04:46.710
I was never taking you
to the store.

04:46.710 --> 04:48.920
Right.
Everyone, get in the car!

04:50.290 --> 04:51.540
Anna-Kat?

04:51.540 --> 04:54.120
Yes, Grandma?
Piece of advice.

04:54.120 --> 04:55.670
Never have kids.

04:55.670 --> 04:56.750
On it.

04:56.750 --> 05:01.580
♪♪

05:01.580 --> 05:04.710
Oliver handed in this birdhouse
yesterday in shop class.

05:04.710 --> 05:06.670
Wow!
You built that?

05:06.670 --> 05:08.500
Great job.
No.

05:08.500 --> 05:10.920
This birdhouse
was purchased at a store.

05:10.920 --> 05:12.580
Oh, no, I don't think
Oliver would do that.

05:12.580 --> 05:15.290
I just bought this
at Izzo's Hardware.

05:15.290 --> 05:16.620
But I really don't
know him that well.

05:16.620 --> 05:17.920
Oliver cheated.

05:19.710 --> 05:22.420
I am so
disappointed in you.

05:22.420 --> 05:24.290
I'm sorry. I tried
building one on my own.

05:24.290 --> 05:25.960
It just kept falling apart.

05:25.960 --> 05:28.380
Oliver will repeat shop class
this summer,

05:28.380 --> 05:29.920
and this will go on
his permanent record.

05:29.920 --> 05:32.120
His one-week suspension
begins immediately.

05:33.460 --> 05:35.420
Immediately?

05:35.420 --> 05:38.080
Is there any way that we
can start it tomorrow?

05:38.080 --> 05:40.330
You see,
today is my day off.

05:40.330 --> 05:43.290
Mrs. Otto, you're talking to a
man who doesn't take days off.

05:43.290 --> 05:45.330
Don't you get
the whole summer off?

05:45.330 --> 05:46.710
Yes.

05:46.710 --> 05:48.120
And a great deal
of holidays.

05:49.830 --> 05:51.420
I'm so screwed.

05:51.420 --> 05:53.170
If Harvard ever sees this,
they'll never let me in.
[ Sighs ]

05:53.170 --> 05:54.920
This could destroy
my whole future.

05:54.920 --> 05:56.920
Well, you should have thought
of that before you cheated.

05:56.920 --> 05:58.250
Now I'm gonna be stuck
at some dead-end

05:58.250 --> 06:00.580
loserville university
like...

06:00.580 --> 06:02.290
ugh, Cornell.

06:02.290 --> 06:05.580
I can't believe
you did that.

06:05.580 --> 06:07.580
You always say cheating
is the sign of a winner.

06:07.580 --> 06:08.830
I never say that.

06:11.170 --> 06:14.380
Anna-Kat, I just saw you take
out money from under the board.

06:14.380 --> 06:16.210
Cheating is not okay.

06:16.210 --> 06:18.710
But Mama says it is.
I never said that.

06:18.710 --> 06:24.540
♪♪

06:24.540 --> 06:26.080
She cheated!
So?

06:26.080 --> 06:27.460
What do you mean, "so"?
She cheated!

06:27.460 --> 06:29.170
Kids today don't even
understand winning

06:29.170 --> 06:31.250
because everyone is given
a stupid trophy.

06:31.250 --> 06:33.210
So, if she wants to win and
breaks a few rules to do it,

06:33.210 --> 06:34.830
I don't see
a problem with it.

06:34.830 --> 06:37.710
I think that's gonna come back
and bite us on the ass.

06:37.710 --> 06:38.540
Mnh-mnh.

06:38.540 --> 06:41.080
Ohhh.

06:41.080 --> 06:43.750
Ohhhh.

06:43.750 --> 06:44.830
What am I gonna do?

06:44.830 --> 06:46.540
We'll talk to your dad
and figure it out.

06:46.540 --> 06:47.710
You're gonna tell Dad?

06:47.710 --> 06:48.880
Of course
I'm gonna tell him.

06:48.880 --> 06:50.620
I wouldn't.
He's definitely gonna blame you.

06:50.620 --> 06:52.540
Hey!
I'm not the one who cheated.

06:52.540 --> 06:55.120
You did.
You're the one who's in trouble.

06:55.120 --> 06:57.170
And you got suspended
on my day off.

06:57.170 --> 06:59.580
Now all my important plans
are ruined.

06:59.580 --> 07:01.580
You get to watch TV while
I'm home from school.

07:01.580 --> 07:03.120
Not with my pants off,
I can't!

07:03.120 --> 07:08.250
♪♪

07:08.250 --> 07:10.170
Nice delivery, Taylor.

07:10.170 --> 07:11.290
Thanks, Grandma.

07:11.290 --> 07:13.040
You have the potential
to lead

07:13.040 --> 07:15.790
the glamorous life
of a stewardess.

07:15.790 --> 07:17.710
Kathryn, they now prefer to be
called flight attendants.

07:17.710 --> 07:19.790
Flight attendants?

07:19.790 --> 07:22.170
Oh. [ Scoffs ]
Please.

07:22.170 --> 07:24.960
You know, everything was perfect
before the lawsuit,

07:24.960 --> 07:27.460
then they started hiring
all those uggos.

07:29.250 --> 07:31.920
You said you came here to help,
but you're not helping.

07:31.920 --> 07:33.460
You're the worst influence.

07:33.460 --> 07:34.880
You know what?

07:34.880 --> 07:36.790
I think I need
a bigger glass.

07:38.210 --> 07:39.830
She is helping!

07:39.830 --> 07:42.540
She's helping me come up with
another plan other than college.

07:42.540 --> 07:44.460
There is no other plan.
College is the plan.

07:44.460 --> 07:46.000
You're studying
for the S.A.T.s.

07:46.000 --> 07:47.710
We're your parents,
and we know what's best for you.

07:47.710 --> 07:49.330
Speaking of, Greg,

07:49.330 --> 07:50.880
you should know what happened
with Principal Ablin

07:50.880 --> 07:52.040
at school today.

07:53.540 --> 07:55.170
[ Luthor chewing ]

07:55.170 --> 07:57.120
Anna-Kat, that's not how
we finish our dinner.

07:57.120 --> 07:58.380
But Mama always says --

07:58.380 --> 08:00.290
Let's not "Mama always says"
right now.

08:00.290 --> 08:02.000
Well, at least you're
not like your mom,

08:02.000 --> 08:04.540
giving them advice that's gonna
totally derail their lives.

08:04.540 --> 08:06.620
Oh [bleep]

08:06.620 --> 08:08.540
So, what did Principal Ablin
want to tell you?

08:09.960 --> 08:11.330
Oliver's getting an award.

08:13.620 --> 08:16.040
Oh.
[ Blender whirs, shuts off ]

08:17.500 --> 08:19.170
Mom, that's a vase.

08:20.330 --> 08:21.710
Yeah.

08:28.460 --> 08:31.460
Instead of cooking meals
or helping with laundry,

08:31.460 --> 08:34.580
my mom is telling Taylor
to do what she did --

08:34.580 --> 08:37.420
not go to college and trade
on her looks and body.

08:37.420 --> 08:39.250
Moms are the worst.

08:39.250 --> 08:40.880
You know, my mom
is scared of dogs,

08:40.880 --> 08:42.710
which is why I bought
German Shepherds

08:42.710 --> 08:44.500
and asked for them
to be extra German.

08:44.500 --> 08:46.080
Well, my mom couldn't be
more helpful.

08:46.080 --> 08:47.330
She cooks, she cleans --

08:47.330 --> 08:49.080
Shut up.
Stop talking right now.

08:49.080 --> 08:50.880
If you don't have anything
destructive to say,

08:50.880 --> 08:52.380
don't say anything at all.

08:52.380 --> 08:54.290
And what am I going to
do about Oliver?

08:54.290 --> 08:57.080
I have to hide his suspension
until I can fix it.

08:57.080 --> 08:59.250
Otherwise,
Greg is going to blame me.

08:59.250 --> 09:01.620
Ugh!
That kid is such an idiot.

09:01.620 --> 09:03.120
Can I order something?

09:03.120 --> 09:05.580
Cheaters get the garnish.

09:06.670 --> 09:08.040
That's it.

09:08.040 --> 09:09.460
Well, I have to go to work.

09:09.460 --> 09:11.380
Yep, me, too.

09:11.380 --> 09:13.710
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
You can't come with me.

09:13.710 --> 09:16.330
I have to go throw a kid's
first birthday party,

09:16.330 --> 09:19.210
and you can't go home
because Dad might see you.

09:19.210 --> 09:22.380
So, Doris is going
to look after you.

09:24.040 --> 09:25.540
No. No, Mom, please.

09:25.540 --> 09:27.040
Anything else.
Pick a bone, you can break it.

09:27.040 --> 09:28.540
Sorry.

09:28.540 --> 09:31.710
Next time, just build
the stupid birdhouse.

09:35.170 --> 09:37.210
I want you
to meet my dogs.

09:37.210 --> 09:39.540
I even have
an outfit for you.

09:39.540 --> 09:41.420
[ Dog growling ]
Call him off!

09:41.420 --> 09:43.580
No, he likes you!
He's just playing!

09:43.580 --> 09:46.710
[ Dogs barking ]

09:48.790 --> 09:50.830
Oh, Principal Ablin!

09:50.830 --> 09:53.210
What a surprise
bumping into you.

09:53.210 --> 09:55.120
This is my office.
I'm always here.

09:55.120 --> 09:56.880
Well, I was just in
the neighborhood,

09:56.880 --> 09:59.710
and I thought I would
drop off some cupcakes

09:59.710 --> 10:02.120
that I made just for you.

10:05.580 --> 10:07.710
You can't bribe me
with cupcakes!

10:07.710 --> 10:09.620
Especially not with that
frosting-to-cake ratio!

10:11.500 --> 10:13.380
I like more frosting.

10:13.380 --> 10:17.210
So, I guess this balloon sword
doesn't do anything for you?

10:17.210 --> 10:18.330
No.

10:26.750 --> 10:28.290
Vvvr!

10:28.290 --> 10:30.620
[ Screaming ]

10:30.620 --> 10:33.620
[ Dogs barking ]

10:33.620 --> 10:36.420
I'd call them off,
but they're totally untrained!

10:36.420 --> 10:38.920
♪♪

10:38.920 --> 10:40.580
You know, even though
you're showing

10:40.580 --> 10:42.000
a lot of natural ability,

10:42.000 --> 10:44.330
you don't want to become
a stewardess right away.

10:44.330 --> 10:46.170
Yes, I do.
It's the best job in the world.

10:46.170 --> 10:47.460
Well, of course it is.

10:47.460 --> 10:50.670
But first,
just take a few years off.

10:50.670 --> 10:53.330
You know, Dubai wasn't really
popping when I was young,

10:53.330 --> 10:55.750
but it seems like a fun place
to make mistakes.

10:55.750 --> 10:57.040
This.

10:57.040 --> 10:58.620
This is my college
right here.

11:00.710 --> 11:02.710
Why are you here again?

11:02.710 --> 11:04.830
Oh, I just missed you
and the kids terribly.

11:06.290 --> 11:07.880
I'm serious.
Ugh.

11:07.880 --> 11:09.460
I'm serious.

11:09.460 --> 11:10.790
[ Exhales sharply ]

11:10.790 --> 11:13.380
I'm serious.

11:13.380 --> 11:15.080
Well, you're just gonna
have to believe me.

11:15.080 --> 11:16.750
Well, you need to
stop putting

11:16.750 --> 11:18.710
terrible ideas into
my daughter's head.

11:18.710 --> 11:20.330
Well, at least I'm putting
something in her head.

11:20.330 --> 11:21.710
What is that supposed
to mean?!

11:21.710 --> 11:23.920
I don't know,
I'm just firing back!

11:25.830 --> 11:27.920
So...

11:27.920 --> 11:29.710
how was your day?

11:29.710 --> 11:31.250
Really, Mom?

11:31.250 --> 11:32.460
Like I couldn't
hear you laughing

11:32.460 --> 11:34.000
over FaceTime with Doris?

11:34.000 --> 11:36.120
I talked to Principal Ablin,
he's still not budging,

11:36.120 --> 11:38.380
and your dad cannot find out
about your suspension.

11:38.380 --> 11:42.290
So, you're gonna spend a couple
more days with Doris.

11:42.290 --> 11:44.620
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

11:44.620 --> 11:46.000
Dad, I got suspended.

11:47.040 --> 11:48.580
I can't go back there.

11:48.580 --> 11:50.120
Suspended?

11:50.120 --> 11:52.330
I cheated in shop class.
How?!

11:52.330 --> 11:54.960
I bought a birdhouse
and passed it off as my own.

11:54.960 --> 11:57.040
I'm so disappointed
in myself.

11:57.040 --> 11:59.500
But you know who I'm more
disappointed in?

11:59.500 --> 12:01.710
Mom.

12:01.710 --> 12:03.380
For setting such
a bad example.

12:03.380 --> 12:04.880
Hey!

12:04.880 --> 12:06.920
No, you let our kids know

12:06.920 --> 12:09.330
it was okay to cheat, and now
they're paying the price.

12:09.330 --> 12:10.620
Plus, you tried to
keep it from me.

12:10.620 --> 12:12.880
In my defense, I keep tons
of things from you.

12:12.880 --> 12:14.040
Wh--

12:14.040 --> 12:15.380
If Harvard ever finds out,

12:15.380 --> 12:16.540
there's no way
I'm getting in.

12:16.540 --> 12:18.040
I tried talking to
Principal Ablin,

12:18.040 --> 12:19.420
and he still
wouldn't listen.

12:19.420 --> 12:21.210
What am I gonna do, Dad?

12:21.210 --> 12:24.210
I'll talk to Ablin,
educator to educator.

12:24.210 --> 12:25.750
But before that,
you're gonna have to do what

12:25.750 --> 12:27.080
you should have done
in the first place.

12:27.080 --> 12:28.210
You're gonna build
that birdhouse.

12:28.210 --> 12:30.080
I don't care if it
takes you all night.

12:32.040 --> 12:33.170
Here, Mama.

12:35.080 --> 12:36.460
I don't want
my dolls anymore.

12:36.460 --> 12:38.040
But you're their mommy.

12:38.040 --> 12:40.290
I was,
but Grandma's right.

12:40.290 --> 12:41.710
I'm not having kids.

12:41.710 --> 12:43.960
They're not worth it.

12:43.960 --> 12:45.920
So many disappointments.

12:45.920 --> 12:50.670
♪♪

12:55.170 --> 12:56.540
Educator to educator,
give him another chance.

12:56.540 --> 12:58.250
After all,
it's only shop class.

13:00.710 --> 13:03.250
I have had enough of all
this shop-class bashing.

13:03.250 --> 13:05.670
You may mock it --
No, I wasn't mocking.

13:05.670 --> 13:08.670
Shop class is an essential
part of the curriculum.

13:08.670 --> 13:10.120
I understand that.
I was only saying that --

13:10.120 --> 13:11.670
I myself was a very
poor student,

13:11.670 --> 13:14.040
but I found myself
in shop class.

13:14.040 --> 13:16.920
The smell of sawdust,
the whir of the miter saw.

13:16.920 --> 13:18.790
I built this desk myself.

13:18.790 --> 13:20.790
In fact, everything
you see in this room,

13:20.790 --> 13:22.540
built with my own
two hands.

13:25.170 --> 13:26.460
I can't tell
if you're joking.

13:26.460 --> 13:28.670
You can show yourself
out the door.

13:28.670 --> 13:30.170
That I also built!

13:30.170 --> 13:31.120
Okay.

13:34.250 --> 13:35.880
This class was supposed
to be an easy "A,"

13:35.880 --> 13:38.170
and instead it ruined
everything!
I'm sorry, Oliver.

13:38.170 --> 13:39.880
Sometimes you have
to just own up

13:39.880 --> 13:42.210
and take responsibility
for your actions.
Mm-hmm.

13:42.210 --> 13:43.330
Isn't that right, honey?

13:44.880 --> 13:47.460
I texted you a frowny face
and a heart.

13:47.460 --> 13:49.420
How much more responsibility
can I take?

13:49.420 --> 13:53.710
Oliver, you could always become
a stewardess with Taylor.

13:53.710 --> 13:56.710
You can pick a fun hub, you two
could get an apartment together.

13:56.710 --> 13:59.040
Uh, maybe work for Lufthansa,

13:59.040 --> 14:00.540
the Harvard of the airlines.

14:00.540 --> 14:01.580
Oh, look.

14:01.580 --> 14:03.080
The captain just turned on

14:03.080 --> 14:04.790
the "Shut Your
Friggin' Mouth" sign.

14:04.790 --> 14:06.960
Mom, I'm gonna
ask you again.

14:06.960 --> 14:08.750
Why are you even here?

14:08.750 --> 14:10.750
Like I said -- to visit.

14:10.750 --> 14:12.580
You never just come
for a visit.

14:12.580 --> 14:15.620
And because I rented
my apartment

14:15.620 --> 14:17.620
to some Germans on Airbnb.

14:17.620 --> 14:18.620
You rented
your apartment?

14:18.620 --> 14:19.830
For how long?

14:19.830 --> 14:21.540
Oh, that's tough to say.

14:21.540 --> 14:22.880
It could be a while.

14:22.880 --> 14:25.000
Yeah, the Germans seem
to be putting down roots.

14:25.000 --> 14:27.620
One of them is running
for city council.

14:27.620 --> 14:30.040
Why in the world would you
rent your apartment out?

14:30.040 --> 14:31.330
Well, if you must know,

14:31.330 --> 14:34.380
my pension from Pan Am
didn't exactly pan out.

14:34.380 --> 14:36.540
Are you broke?
Not broke.

14:36.540 --> 14:39.290
No, I am definitely keeping
the Germans' security deposit.

14:39.290 --> 14:40.750
I can't believe it.

14:40.750 --> 14:44.210
Your life is a mess and you
are giving my kids advice?

14:45.580 --> 14:46.750
I was just trying to help!

14:46.750 --> 14:48.380
Always in the wrong ways!

14:48.380 --> 14:50.580
Oh, like you're so
great yourself!

14:50.580 --> 14:53.040
Yeah, you always complain about
Grandma being a bad influence,

14:53.040 --> 14:55.250
but the apple didn't
fall far from the sauce.

14:55.250 --> 14:56.670
Yeah, you don't need
to go to college.

14:56.670 --> 14:57.670
You're all set.

14:59.170 --> 15:00.920
You know, Taylor
makes a good point.

15:02.290 --> 15:04.330
You're judging your mom
for being a poor influence

15:04.330 --> 15:07.210
on the kids, and she is,
but you're just as bad.

15:08.540 --> 15:09.670
That is not true.

15:09.670 --> 15:11.250
It totally is.

15:11.250 --> 15:13.170
You condone cheating,
manipulation,

15:13.170 --> 15:14.830
grape-stealing in
the supermarket.

15:14.830 --> 15:16.040
Oh, that isn't stealing.

15:16.040 --> 15:18.040
No, that's hospitality

15:18.040 --> 15:20.670
that is factored into
the cost of doing business.

15:20.670 --> 15:22.540
Stealing grapes with my kids

15:22.540 --> 15:24.710
was the only thing
I was looking forward to.

15:24.710 --> 15:26.460
Now that's bad?

15:26.460 --> 15:28.540
Feeling really good about
dying a spinster.

15:29.620 --> 15:31.120
Right there.

15:31.120 --> 15:33.540
Generational bad influence
in action.

15:33.540 --> 15:34.420
You're like your mom.

15:34.420 --> 15:36.380
Well, what do you know?

15:36.380 --> 15:38.330
You grew up to be
just like me.

15:41.380 --> 15:44.120
[ Retching ]

15:44.120 --> 15:45.080
[ Sighs ]

15:45.080 --> 15:46.920
I think that's all of it.

15:46.920 --> 15:47.880
[ Toilet flushes ]

15:47.880 --> 15:48.750
All she said was --

15:48.750 --> 15:50.380
Greg, please.

15:50.380 --> 15:53.210
I don't have anything left
to throw up.

15:53.210 --> 15:58.420
I have dedicated my life to
not being like my mother.

15:58.420 --> 16:00.080
How did this happen?

16:00.080 --> 16:01.670
Listen,
it happened to me, too.

16:01.670 --> 16:03.500
I never wanted to be
like my dad.

16:03.500 --> 16:05.920
Next thing you know, I'm putting
an "I Brake for Chaucer"

16:05.920 --> 16:07.290
bumper sticker
on my attache.

16:07.290 --> 16:08.000
[ Sighs ]

16:09.380 --> 16:11.750
Is everything okay?

16:11.750 --> 16:13.380
Oh, my God.

16:13.380 --> 16:15.250
I am just like her.

16:15.250 --> 16:18.580
I always ask if everything's
okay without really caring.

16:18.580 --> 16:19.960
I care.

16:21.380 --> 16:22.420
Oh, my God.

16:22.420 --> 16:23.920
I'm just like my mother.

16:25.250 --> 16:27.330
I double down even
when I'm lying.

16:27.330 --> 16:28.670
So, this behavior
is hereditary.

16:28.670 --> 16:30.210
It's in the genes.

16:30.210 --> 16:32.250
Some families pass on
high blood pressure.

16:32.250 --> 16:33.710
Yours passes on
terribleness.

16:33.710 --> 16:35.920
Mom, Greg might be
onto something.

16:35.920 --> 16:37.330
This has got to stop.

16:37.330 --> 16:40.170
I cannot pass this down
to my kids.

16:40.170 --> 16:42.880
You're right.
No, this ends today.

16:42.880 --> 16:45.830
Do you really mean that,
or are you just doubling down?

16:45.830 --> 16:47.920
I don't even know
anymore.

16:47.920 --> 16:50.960
Listen, I recognize
the situation that you're in

16:50.960 --> 16:52.960
is partially my fault.

16:54.250 --> 16:56.120
The whole "cheating
is for winners" thing

16:56.120 --> 16:58.540
might have been
a mixed message.

16:58.540 --> 17:01.040
Yeah, but I also should've
been smart enough

17:01.040 --> 17:03.080
not to cheat when I want
to go to Harvard.

17:03.080 --> 17:04.620
What am I gonna do?

17:04.620 --> 17:06.620
What you're gonna do
is not let one mistake

17:06.620 --> 17:08.120
derail your whole life.

17:08.120 --> 17:12.250
And, Taylor, I may not have
given you the best advice.

17:12.250 --> 17:14.040
What are you talking about?
Your life was awesome.

17:14.040 --> 17:17.250
It was.
Oh, it really was.

17:17.250 --> 17:19.290
[ Chuckles ]
Trust me, you get a chance

17:19.290 --> 17:21.330
to spend a weekend in Tahiti
with Ricardo Montalban,

17:21.330 --> 17:22.420
you take it.

17:22.420 --> 17:24.250
[ Chuckles ]
Story for another time.

17:24.250 --> 17:26.290
Mm-hmm.
The point is...

17:26.290 --> 17:27.460
[ Sighs ]

17:27.460 --> 17:29.120
You need to go
to college.

17:29.120 --> 17:30.420
What for?

17:30.420 --> 17:31.960
I mean, I'll just do
what you did.

17:31.960 --> 17:33.250
Your life was amazing.

17:33.250 --> 17:35.830
Uh-huh, but if you
go to college,

17:35.830 --> 17:38.120
then you'll have other
options for when your airline

17:38.120 --> 17:40.500
goes bankrupt, taking your
pension with it,

17:40.500 --> 17:43.500
and you won't wind up
broke with six Germans

17:43.500 --> 17:46.210
crammed in your apartment
ordering weird movies

17:46.210 --> 17:48.380
with your iTunes
like "FernGully"

17:48.380 --> 17:50.920
while you're two states away,
sponging off your kid.

17:50.920 --> 17:52.830
[ Sighs ]

17:52.830 --> 17:56.080
It's just a real good idea
to have a back-up plan

17:56.080 --> 17:58.790
'cause you might not be
as lucky as me

17:58.790 --> 18:02.500
and get a daughter
like I did.

18:02.500 --> 18:05.750
And then I can visit you
in college.

18:07.460 --> 18:09.120
Oh, frat boys love me.

18:09.120 --> 18:10.920
[ Sighs ]

18:10.920 --> 18:11.710
Right?
Yeah. Yeah.

18:14.040 --> 18:15.710
Well,
if I go to Cornell,

18:15.710 --> 18:17.290
I'll be next
to Niagara Falls,

18:17.290 --> 18:18.750
so when I get too depressed,
I'll just hop in a barrel

18:18.750 --> 18:20.380
and throw myself over.

18:20.380 --> 18:23.540
Oliver, why do you have to be
so melancholy all the time?

18:23.540 --> 18:25.120
Wait,
did I use that right?

18:26.670 --> 18:28.290
I did.

18:28.290 --> 18:29.580
Oh, no!

18:29.580 --> 18:31.790
I'm learning things.

18:31.790 --> 18:33.080
How long is your mom
gonna sleep?

18:33.080 --> 18:34.620
I have to get into my office
sometime today.

18:34.620 --> 18:36.880
Mm.
She and Mama have
so much in common

18:36.880 --> 18:39.540
that maybe if we open up
a package of cinnamon rolls,

18:39.540 --> 18:40.880
she'll wake up, too.

18:40.880 --> 18:42.420
[ Door opens ]
[ Giggles ]

18:45.170 --> 18:47.580
Well, I better be going.
[ Chuckles ]

18:47.580 --> 18:49.710
Thank you, Kathryn,
for an unforgettable night.

18:49.710 --> 18:53.120
Oh, no, thank you,
Principal Abs-lin.

18:53.120 --> 18:54.500
Ohhh.

18:54.500 --> 18:56.710
Yeah.
Okay, then.

18:56.710 --> 18:58.380
[ Laughs ]

18:58.380 --> 19:00.920
Oliver,
your record is wiped clean.

19:02.290 --> 19:05.000
I did a little
woodworking of my own.

19:05.000 --> 19:06.580
Grandma,
you're the best.

19:06.580 --> 19:08.500
Oh.

19:08.500 --> 19:10.460
See? I told you
I could be helpful.

19:10.460 --> 19:11.790
That was some move.

19:11.790 --> 19:13.290
You don't think you
got into Duke

19:13.290 --> 19:16.120
just because of your
field hockey, do you?

19:16.120 --> 19:17.960
Honey...

19:17.960 --> 19:19.080
[ Snickers ]

19:19.080 --> 19:26.330
♪♪

19:26.330 --> 19:28.380
Just because Nana
used her nah-nah

19:28.380 --> 19:30.290
to get you off the hook
with Principal Ablin

19:30.290 --> 19:32.670
doesn't mean you're
off the hook for cheating.

19:32.670 --> 19:33.920
So, what is it?

19:33.920 --> 19:36.580
I'm grounded, no screens,
blah, blah, blah?

19:36.580 --> 19:37.960
No.

19:37.960 --> 19:40.000
Something much worse.

19:41.290 --> 19:45.750
So, bell is to church
as horn is to...

19:45.750 --> 19:46.960
rhinoceros?

19:46.960 --> 19:49.170
No. Car.

19:49.170 --> 19:51.670
I'm pretty sure a rhino's
the one with the horn.

19:51.670 --> 19:53.250
This is inhumane.

19:53.250 --> 19:56.250
Mom and Dad said it was your
punishment to tutor me.

19:56.250 --> 19:58.460
Mom, I beg you,
anything else.

19:58.460 --> 20:00.790
It'd be easier to teach
Luthor how to juggle.

20:00.790 --> 20:04.120
I'll give you a choice --
it's either this...

20:04.120 --> 20:06.580
or Doris.

20:06.580 --> 20:09.500
♪♪

20:09.500 --> 20:11.040
[ Screaming ]

20:11.040 --> 20:14.120
[ Dogs barking, growling ]

20:14.120 --> 20:16.830
[ Laughs ]

20:16.830 --> 20:19.290
This is still better!

20:19.290 --> 20:20.250
Release the bees.

20:24.420 --> 20:26.250
[ School bell rings ]

20:26.250 --> 20:27.620
Hey, champ.

20:27.620 --> 20:29.960
[ Chuckles ]

20:29.960 --> 20:32.500
So, did your, uh, grandma
say anything about me?

20:32.500 --> 20:34.580
No, she's been busy.

20:34.580 --> 20:35.960
Oh. Cool.

20:35.960 --> 20:37.000
I've been busy, too.

20:40.790 --> 20:42.790
Okay, um, I've got
to get going.

20:42.790 --> 20:44.460
Math class.

20:44.460 --> 20:45.790
See you around,
Principal Ablin.

20:45.790 --> 20:47.380
You know what?

20:47.380 --> 20:49.750
You can go ahead
and call me Grandpa Ablin.

20:49.750 --> 20:52.330
I-I don't want
to do that.

20:52.330 --> 20:53.540
Gramps?
No.

20:53.540 --> 20:54.830
Pappy?

20:54.830 --> 20:55.670
It's more folksy.

20:56.960 --> 20:58.620
Don't worry,
we'll find it.

20:58.620 --> 21:04.540
♪♪

21:04.540 --> 21:06.080
That's my boy.

21:06.080 --> 21:07.500
[ Door closes ]

21:07.500 --> 21:08.880
Hey, not so hard.

21:08.880 --> 21:11.170
I built that door.

21:11.170 --> 21:12.920
I built this whole school.

21:15.920 --> 21:16.880
Mm.

21:16.880 --> 21:20.080
♪♪
